headline: Genuine Parts (NYSE:GPC) Sees Q4 2024 Earnings Decline
summary: Genuine Parts (NYSE:GPC) reported its earnings for Q4 2024, revealing a decline in net income compared to the previous year. Despite an increase in sales, the company observed a reduction in its earnings per share, which was reflected in its share price declining 9% last quarter. The company's announcement of a quarterly dividend and share repurchase program may provide some steadiness, but broader market turbulence, characterized by a 12% decline over the same period, has likely influenced...

headline: Buying the Dip: 3 Super Safe High-Yield Dividend Stocks I Added to My Retirement Account During the Stock Market Sell-Off.
summary: The stock market recently took a big dip, driven down by concerns about how much tariffs will affect the economy.  One of the benefits of falling stock prices is that dividend yields move in the opposite direction.

headline: 3 Reasons to Sell GPC and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Genuine Parts has gotten torched over the last six months - since October 2024, its stock price has dropped 22.6% to a new 52-week low of $103.50 per share. This may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
